1867
01:41:56.877 --> 01:41:58.701
Well. damn. Corporal.

1868
01:41:59.270 --> 01:42:02.213
I don't know if you're smart
or just shit nuts.

1869
01:42:02.349 --> 01:42:04.683
You never struck me
as all that smart.

1870
01:42:04.818 --> 01:42:05.876
[warriors chuckle]

1871
01:42:06.011 --> 01:42:08.553
I need your word.
marine to marine.

1872
01:42:08.688 --> 01:42:09.980
Safety

1873
01:42:10.714 --> 01:42:12.281
for these people.

1874
01:42:12.717 --> 01:42:14.320
Burn them all. Quaritch.

1875
01:42:14.456 --> 01:42:16.318
[♪ tense music plays]

1876
01:42:16.454 --> 01:42:17.988
[snarls]

1877
01:42:24.068 --> 01:42:25.633
Do we have a deal?

1878
01:42:29.237 --> 01:42:30.366
[music ends]

1879
01:42:30.501 --> 01:42:31.540
Done.

1880
01:42:32.847 --> 01:42:34.609
Want to pinky swear?

1881
01:42:39.711 --> 01:42:41.682
[breathing heavily]

1882
01:42:43.748 --> 01:42:44.982
[Quaritch] Take him.

1883
01:42:46.518 --> 01:42:47.556
Turn around.

1884
01:42:49.557 --> 01:42:51.758
[Neytiri breathing heavily]

1885
01:42:53.557 --> 01:42:54.596
Move.

1886
01:43:00.938 --> 01:43:02.274
[yells]

1887
01:43:07.079 --> 01:43:09.611
[breathing heavily]

1888
01:43:13.350 --> 01:43:14.715
-Let's go.
-Come on.

1889
01:43:15.680 --> 01:43:16.721
Another time then.

1890
01:43:16.856 --> 01:43:17.786
Mrs. Sully.

1891
01:43:17.922 --> 01:43:19.258
[snarls]

1892
01:43:22.158 --> 01:43:23.327
Saddle up.

1893
01:43:23.463 --> 01:43:25.462
-[Mangkwan whooping]
-[warrior grunts]

1894
01:43:29.332 --> 01:43:31.534
[breathing shakily]

1895
01:44:00.130 --> 01:44:03.335
[beeping]

1896
01:44:06.631 --> 01:44:07.468
What do we got?

1897
01:44:07.603 --> 01:44:09.064
Ma'am. we have
a big incursion.

1898
01:44:09.200 --> 01:44:10.901
-Banshee riders inbound.
-I see that.

1899
01:44:11.037 --> 01:44:12.272
-So light 'em up.
-I can't. ma'am.

1900
01:44:12.408 --> 01:44:13.903
Weapons locked out.

1901
01:44:14.038 --> 01:44:15.743
They all have
IFF badges.

1902
01:44:16.245 --> 01:44:17.281
Expand it.

1903
01:44:17.417 --> 01:44:19.285
Echo 1-6.
intersect the target.

1904
01:44:29.764 --> 01:44:31.121
[shrieks]

1905
01:44:32.766 --> 01:44:33.898
[roars]

1906
01:44:34.033 --> 01:44:35.763
[crowd clamoring]

1907
01:44:39.237 --> 01:44:41.736
[breathing heavily]

1908
01:44:57.924 --> 01:45:00.117
[in Na'vi]

1909
01:45:07.930 --> 01:45:09.332
[scientist. in English]
All right. All right.

1910
01:45:09.467 --> 01:45:10.659
-Hold him there.
-[grunting]

1911
01:45:10.794 --> 01:45:12.331
Easy. easy.

1912
01:45:12.466 --> 01:45:13.537
Let's go.

1913
01:45:15.134 --> 01:45:16.107
-[Spider] Jake!
-[soldier 1] Grab him.

1914
01:45:16.242 --> 01:45:17.505
[soldier 2] Let's go. Move.

1915
01:45:17.640 --> 01:45:20.079
-Jake! Jake!
-Bring him in.

1916
01:45:20.214 --> 01:45:23.649
-[radio chatter]
-[chuckles]

1917
01:45:23.784 --> 01:45:24.779
Jake!

1918
01:45:25.314 --> 01:45:26.550
[soldier 3] Up.

1919
01:45:32.859 --> 01:45:34.085
[grunts]

1920
01:45:41.896 --> 01:45:43.699
Mission accomplished.
General.

1921
01:45:44.234 --> 01:45:45.367
Jake Sully.

1922
01:45:45.502 --> 01:45:47.571
<i> Toruk Makto</i> himself.

1923
01:45:48.040 --> 01:45:49.641
[clamoring]

1924
01:45:50.010 --> 01:45:52.510
[breathing deeply]

1925
01:46:02.149 --> 01:46:04.454
It's not enough for you
to hand out guns.

1926
01:46:04.890 --> 01:46:07.958
you've got to bring hostiles
inside the perimeter.

1927
01:46:08.094 --> 01:46:08.893
[speaks Na'vi]

1928
01:46:09.029 --> 01:46:09.951
[speaks Na'vi]

1929
01:46:10.087 --> 01:46:11.487
[in English] Not hostiles.

1930
01:46:11.623 --> 01:46:12.854
Allies.

1931
01:46:13.457 --> 01:46:16.026
General Ardmore.
I'd like you to meet Varang.

1932
01:46:16.161 --> 01:46:18.228
<i> Tsahik</i> of the<i> Mangkwan</i> .

1933
01:46:21.201 --> 01:46:23.901
Let me make this very clear.
Colonel Cochise.

1934
01:46:24.036 --> 01:46:25.735
I want every one
of these savages

1935
01:46:25.871 --> 01:46:27.570
escorted off my base

1936
01:46:27.705 --> 01:46:28.743
ASAP.

1937
01:46:28.879 --> 01:46:31.241
including your little
missy over here.

1938
01:46:32.787 --> 01:46:34.519
[sighs]

1939
01:46:35.153 --> 01:46:36.955
[inhales deeply]

1940
01:46:37.358 --> 01:46:39.315
Don't be a jackass.
General.

1941
01:46:40.995 --> 01:46:42.318
Take the win.

1942
01:46:44.297 --> 01:46:45.530
We got him.
people!

1943
01:46:46.824 --> 01:46:48.698
Huh? [chuckles]

1944
01:46:49.696 --> 01:46:51.294
End of an era!

1945
01:47:06.645 --> 01:47:07.720
Yeah!

1946
01:47:07.855 --> 01:47:08.784
Whoo!

1947
01:47:09.187 --> 01:47:10.053
<i> Tsahik.</i>

1948
01:47:10.188 --> 01:47:11.417
[chuckles]

1949
01:47:11.552 --> 01:47:12.414
[chuckles]

1950
01:47:12.850 --> 01:47:14.053
Let's go.

1951
01:47:14.789 --> 01:47:17.023
[♪ dramatic music plays]

1952
01:47:29.803 --> 01:47:31.009
[struggling. snarling]

1953
01:47:31.145 --> 01:47:32.511
[nurse] Easy. easy.

1954
01:47:39.245 --> 01:47:41.212
You'll just feel this
a little bit.

1955
01:47:42.147 --> 01:47:43.020
-Hold still.
-[Spider grunts]

1956
01:47:43.155 --> 01:47:44.248
[screams]

1957
01:47:45.785 --> 01:47:46.823
Almost there.

1958
01:47:47.893 --> 01:47:50.155
-Good. Hold it there.
-Another few seconds.

1959
01:47:52.592 --> 01:47:53.631
[growls]

1960
01:47:55.595 --> 01:47:56.634
Payakan!

1961
01:47:57.631 --> 01:47:59.032
[squeaks]

1962
01:48:00.039 --> 01:48:01.265
Payakan!

1963
01:48:08.074 --> 01:48:09.038
[narrating]
<i> The People say</i>

1964
01:48:09.174 --> 01:48:10.947
<i> the sea washes you clean.</i>

1965
01:48:11.083 --> 01:48:12.342
Payakan!

1966
01:48:15.517 --> 01:48:16.253
It's Lo'ak.

1967
01:48:16.388 --> 01:48:17.420
-It's him.
-Lo'ak.

1968
01:48:17.556 --> 01:48:18.818
-[Rotxo] It's him.
-Lo'ak!

1969
01:48:18.954 --> 01:48:19.715
[Aonung]<i> Skxawng</i> . over here.

1970
01:48:19.850 --> 01:48:20.792
Lo'ak!

1971
01:48:20.928 --> 01:48:21.817
Tsireya!

1972
01:48:21.952 --> 01:48:24.090
[honking]

1973
01:48:25.933 --> 01:48:28.727
[Lo'ak]<i> They also say.</i>
<i> if you see the deep ones.</i>

1974
01:48:28.862 --> 01:48:30.228
<i> the</i> Tsyong...

1975
01:48:32.871 --> 01:48:35.167
<i> they're spirits</i>
<i> sent to judge you.</i>

1976
01:48:43.611 --> 01:48:44.473
[squeaks]

1977
01:48:47.620 --> 01:48:49.313
-<i> Tsyong</i> !
-Go. go. go.

1978
01:48:55.457 --> 01:48:56.353
[gasps]

1979
01:49:00.396 --> 01:49:01.292
[grunts]

1980
01:49:13.013 --> 01:49:14.107
[grunts]

1981
01:49:27.556 --> 01:49:29.056
[grunting]

1982
01:49:30.757 --> 01:49:32.059
[straining]

1983
01:49:41.701 --> 01:49:42.773
[grunts]

1984
01:49:50.007 --> 01:49:51.716
[bellows]

1985
01:49:53.087 --> 01:49:55.280
[drowning]

1986
01:50:04.397 --> 01:50:06.460
[echoing] Lo'ak. Lo'ak.

1987
01:50:06.596 --> 01:50:08.425
Lo'ak! Lo'ak!

1988
01:50:08.993 --> 01:50:10.999
[coughing]

1989
01:50:12.798 --> 01:50:13.829
Tsireya.

1990
01:50:14.365 --> 01:50:15.773
-[coughs]
-[chuckles]

1991
01:50:17.242 --> 01:50:18.373
[sighs]

1992
01:50:18.508 --> 01:50:19.467
[chuckles]

1993
01:50:19.603 --> 01:50:21.306
[Tsireya] Thank you.
Great Mother.

1994
01:50:22.108 --> 01:50:22.971
Come on.
let him breathe.

1995
01:50:23.106 --> 01:50:24.039
Let him go.

1996
01:50:24.175 --> 01:50:25.717
[breathing heavily]

1997
01:50:28.315 --> 01:50:29.813
Can't believe you guys
came after me.

1998
01:50:29.948 --> 01:50:31.148
[chuckles]

1999
01:50:31.283 --> 01:50:33.219
My friend's path
is my path.

2000
01:50:36.924 --> 01:50:37.852
Is this your Sister?

2001
01:50:37.988 --> 01:50:39.193
Yes.

2002
01:50:40.163 --> 01:50:42.028
What about Payakan?
Does she hear him?

2003
01:50:42.163 --> 01:50:44.769
He is close.
He is coming now.

2004
01:50:51.479 --> 01:50:52.702
So. what have
you got?

2005
01:50:53.572 --> 01:50:55.780
Uh. this mycelium that's
living inside his body--

2006
01:50:55.915 --> 01:50:57.348
Wait. there's something
living inside of him?

2007
01:50:57.484 --> 01:50:59.244
Yes. it's an endosymbiont.

2008
01:50:59.380 --> 01:51:01.016
It's somehow moderating
the ion exchange--

2009
01:51:01.151 --> 01:51:02.820
Okay. stop. I don't need
to know how it works.

2010
01:51:02.955 --> 01:51:05.251
I just need to know
if we can duplicate it.

2011
01:51:06.654 --> 01:51:07.785
[grunts]

2012
01:51:07.920 --> 01:51:10.991
[grunting]

2013
01:51:11.126 --> 01:51:13.160
Let me out of here.
you jerk-offs!

2014
01:51:14.629 --> 01:51:15.668
[gasps]

2015
01:51:17.298 --> 01:51:18.437
I told those
rubber-gloved pukes

2016
01:51:18.572 --> 01:51:20.468
to lay off you
for a while.

2017
01:51:20.604 --> 01:51:21.630
Where's Jake?

2018
01:51:22.599 --> 01:51:24.570
He's locked up.
where he belongs.

2019
01:51:24.705 --> 01:51:25.744
Here.

2020
01:51:26.809 --> 01:51:28.708
I brought you a burger.

2021
01:51:28.844 --> 01:51:30.011
You better not hurt him.

2022
01:51:30.146 --> 01:51:32.014
He's not part
of your life anymore.

2023
01:51:32.815 --> 01:51:33.943
You're with me now.

2024
01:51:34.078 --> 01:51:35.483
[chuckles]

2025
01:51:35.618 --> 01:51:36.647
I'm your father.

2026
01:51:37.049 --> 01:51:38.179
My father's dead.

2027
01:51:38.749 --> 01:51:41.349
[sighs] You're just
some made-up thing

2028
01:51:41.485 --> 01:51:42.952
they gave
his memories to.

2029
01:51:43.087 --> 01:51:44.727
No. no. No.

2030
01:51:44.862 --> 01:51:47.627
I'm still me.
I checked.

2031
01:51:47.762 --> 01:51:49.031
Yeah. look.

2032
01:51:49.833 --> 01:51:50.925
"Colonel
Miles Quaritch."

2033
01:51:51.061 --> 01:51:52.302
[scoffs]

2034
01:51:52.437 --> 01:51:53.464
Deceased.

2035
01:51:56.234 --> 01:51:57.972
[inhales deeply. sighs]

2036
01:51:58.108 --> 01:51:59.067
You know. we
didn't get a chance

2037
01:51:59.202 --> 01:52:00.637
to talk too much

2038
01:52:00.773 --> 01:52:02.605
when we were out in
the bush together. but. uh...

2039
01:52:04.010 --> 01:52:05.344
I gotta thank you.

2040
01:52:05.480 --> 01:52:08.611
I mean. you hauled me
out of a sunken ship.

2041
01:52:09.620 --> 01:52:10.782
You saved my life.

2042
01:52:11.385 --> 01:52:13.484
Yeah. Sure wish
I hadn't done that.

2043
01:52:15.362 --> 01:52:16.729
Maybe that's true.

2044
01:52:17.863 --> 01:52:19.424
Maybe. deep down.
it isn't.

2045
01:52:19.959 --> 01:52:21.261
Either way.

2046
01:52:21.961 --> 01:52:23.096
I owe you.

2047
01:52:23.232 --> 01:52:26.134
And I gotta tell you
that. uh...

2048
01:52:27.705 --> 01:52:29.500
Man. I'm proud of you.

2049
01:52:31.636 --> 01:52:33.746
You're an amazing kid.
You got...

2050
01:52:34.415 --> 01:52:36.874
guts. smarts. and...

2051
01:52:37.743 --> 01:52:40.181
Son. you've got the heart
of a lion. [chuckles]

2052
01:52:41.546 --> 01:52:44.416
I see myself in you.
Oh. yeah.

2053
01:52:46.188 --> 01:52:48.620
I tell you
who I really see in you.

2054
01:52:49.089 --> 01:52:50.019
and that's your mother.

2055
01:52:50.154 --> 01:52:51.359
[chuckles]

2056
01:52:51.495 --> 01:52:52.220
Oh. man.

2057
01:52:52.356 --> 01:52:55.196
She was. uh. ferocious.

2058
01:52:56.460 --> 01:52:58.331
Tough to live with. but...

2059
01:52:59.900 --> 01:53:01.001
I loved her.

2060
01:53:01.137 --> 01:53:03.776
And. man.
did she love you.

2061
01:53:06.372 --> 01:53:07.670
Hardest thing
she ever did

2062
01:53:07.805 --> 01:53:09.776
was climbing aboard
that gunship that day.

2063
01:53:09.911 --> 01:53:11.173
going into battle.

2064
01:53:11.709 --> 01:53:13.843
leaving her
little baby behind.

2065
01:53:13.979 --> 01:53:15.315
[sighs]

2066
01:53:16.514 --> 01:53:18.648
Your mom died
a hero. Son.

2067
01:53:20.558 --> 01:53:21.490
You got that

2068
01:53:21.625 --> 01:53:22.652
in you too.

2069
01:53:24.891 --> 01:53:25.759
Anyway.

2070
01:53:25.895 --> 01:53:27.028
I didn't come down here

2071
01:53:27.164 --> 01:53:28.560
to take a trip down
memory lane.

2072
01:53:28.695 --> 01:53:31.001
I just came by to tell you
that I'm here for you.

2073
01:53:32.031 --> 01:53:34.532
If you need me.

2074
01:53:36.872 --> 01:53:38.239
I'm here for you.

2075
01:53:41.910 --> 01:53:43.178
Can I keep it?

2076
01:53:53.824 --> 01:53:55.256
Eat something. will you?

2077
01:54:06.571 --> 01:54:07.598
[Lo'ak] Brother!

2078
01:54:12.478 --> 01:54:14.110
[singing]

2079
01:54:14.779 --> 01:54:16.445
I See you. Brother.

2080
01:54:16.847 --> 01:54:19.742
-[panting]
-[moans]

2081
01:54:22.653 --> 01:54:23.519
What is it?

2082
01:54:23.655 --> 01:54:24.615
What's wrong?

2083
01:54:25.249 --> 01:54:26.617
[rumbling]

2084
01:54:29.653 --> 01:54:31.622
Didn't you find
your birth clan?

2085
01:54:32.058 --> 01:54:33.690
[singing]

2086
01:54:45.511 --> 01:54:47.572
[singing]

2087
01:55:00.059 --> 01:55:01.383
<i> Tulkun</i> are
already coming in.

2088
01:55:02.085 --> 01:55:05.026
but the aggregation doesn't
peak until the eclipse.

2089
01:55:05.161 --> 01:55:06.895
which is the day
after tomorrow.

2090
01:55:07.031 --> 01:55:08.893
and that's
when we hit 'em.

2091
01:55:09.329 --> 01:55:11.095
No. no. hold on.
No...

2092
01:55:11.230 --> 01:55:13.301
-you're talking about
wholesale slaughter.
-[Scoresby] Uh-huh.

2093
01:55:13.437 --> 01:55:15.466
Hundreds killed.
Entire pods just wiped out.

2094
01:55:15.601 --> 01:55:17.602
That's the beauty
of the idea.

2095
01:55:17.737 --> 01:55:19.338
We'll fill a year's quota
in just one day.

2096
01:55:19.474 --> 01:55:21.771
These are intelligent.
soulful beings.

2097
01:55:22.240 --> 01:55:23.275
Who are you?

2098
01:55:23.610 --> 01:55:26.479
Ian... Ian Garvin.
Marine biologist.

2099
01:55:28.521 --> 01:55:29.414
These creatures.

2100
01:55:29.549 --> 01:55:31.184
they have culture.
they have music.

2101
01:55:31.319 --> 01:55:32.556
they have names
for each other.

2102
01:55:32.691 --> 01:55:33.516
This is organized.

2103
01:55:33.651 --> 01:55:35.421
This aggregation
is deliberate.

2104
01:55:35.556 --> 01:55:37.795
It's a spiritual gathering
for them--

2105
01:55:37.930 --> 01:55:39.058
Get off your high horse.
Garvin.

2106
01:55:39.193 --> 01:55:40.260
We all made our deals.

2107
01:55:40.396 --> 01:55:42.193
No. I did not sign up
for this!

2108
01:55:42.328 --> 01:55:43.326
[Ardmore] Dr. Garvin.

2109
01:55:43.461 --> 01:55:44.527
Dr. Garvin. thank you.

2110
01:55:44.662 --> 01:55:46.134
Your protest
has been noted.

2111
01:55:46.270 --> 01:55:48.039
-Oh. it's been noted?
-[Ardmore] Yes.

2112
01:55:48.875 --> 01:55:50.500
Sub teams
and fast boats.

2113
01:55:50.636 --> 01:55:52.943
you guys will form
a cordon.

2114
01:55:53.078 --> 01:55:54.409
You'll drive
the family groups

2115
01:55:54.544 --> 01:55:56.745
in here to where it forms
a natural choke point

2116
01:55:56.881 --> 01:55:58.313
against the islands.

2117
01:56:07.390 --> 01:56:08.693
[crowd member]
We got you. Sully!

2118
01:56:08.828 --> 01:56:10.292
I can't believe we got him.

2119
01:56:11.931 --> 01:56:13.328
[guard] Hey!
Make a hole.

2120
01:56:14.932 --> 01:56:16.166
[Quaritch] Open up.

2121
01:56:17.330 --> 01:56:18.564
[guard 2] Weapon. sir.

2122
01:56:27.307 --> 01:56:29.080
End of the line. Jake.

2123
01:56:29.614 --> 01:56:30.374
[sighs]

2124
01:56:30.510 --> 01:56:32.017
[Quaritch] Zero-six tomorrow.

2125
01:56:34.281 --> 01:56:35.686
Varang wants your heart.

2126
01:56:35.822 --> 01:56:38.321
but I'm going old-school.

2127
01:56:38.757 --> 01:56:39.883
Firing squad.

2128
01:56:40.819 --> 01:56:43.627
Selfridge says
it's a "better optic."

2129
01:56:44.363 --> 01:56:46.757
Yeah. Well. you be
a good dog for the suits.

2130
01:56:49.100 --> 01:56:50.598
This isn't
about them.

2131
01:56:50.734 --> 01:56:52.367
